When data comes with a package, it will usually be documented. You can read the documentation for a dataset (or a function) by running ?<name> (just like you run any other line of code either Ctrl + Enter or type it into the console directly).

Question 6:

Why do these two graphs look the same?

ggplot(data = mpg, aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) + 
  geom_point() + 
  geom_smooth()
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula 'y ~ x'

ggplot() + 
  geom_point(data = mpg, aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) + 
  geom_smooth(data = mpg, aes(x = displ, y = hwy))
